58:00',NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'','','','',''),(10,1,NULL,5,NULL,'GG',NULL,'PARRS Filer Crash',NULL,'1','N/A',NULL,'2006-12-29 00:00:00',NULL,'8:35 AM',NULL,'INT','C',NULL,'L',40,13,'The filer for the incoming PARRS interface crashed in PRODGGM.','Marc skipped the first msg on the queue (# 8131818 - SIU^S14^SIU_S12 Appt Modification) and was able to successfully start the filer again.  The skipped msg included an update to the Appt display notes (NTE-3 stored in EPT-7050) for a prenatal Appt on 1/16/07.  Since there was no Cache error logged, Epic reviewed the interface filing code for the NTE segment and we could not determine why the filer had crashed.  So, I resubmitted the skipped msg and it was processed successfully as item EPT-7050 was appropriately updated and the interface filer remained running.','','','','','','',40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-03 10:16:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(11,1,NULL,0,NULL,'CA',NULL,'Prod Outage to Improve Performance and Stability',NULL,'','',NULL,'2006-12-30 00:00:00',NULL,'2:30 AM',NULL,'INT','C',NULL,'M',40,13,'There was an emergency 1-hour FULL OUTAGE for KPHC users in all KPHC hospitals (EXCEPT Hayward, Fremont, Modesto and Fresno) on early Saturday morning, December 30th from 2:30am-3:30am.  The technical team was working to improve KPHC system storage infrastructure.','','','KPHC Leadership communicated the outage to the facilities on Thursday, 12/28/2006.','','','Facilities Impacted: KPHC Users in SRO, SRF, SFO, SSF, RWC, STR, WCR, VAL, ROS, SAC, SSC\r\nFacilities NOT Impacted: HAY, FRE, OAK, RCH, MOD, FRS, SCL\r\n\r\nThe outage started at 2:30 AM and all environments were returned to the end users at 3:00 AM, 30 minutes early.  PRODCAM, PRODSBM, PRODGGM and PRODNBM were all brought down, so interfaces on those deployments were down for roughly 30 mins.  The interfaces on PRODEBM and PRODCCM were left running.  I logged in at 2:50 AM and had all the interfaces on the four affected deployments back up by 2:55 AM with no issues.','',40,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-03 10:26:00','2007-01-03 11:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(12,1,NULL,7,NULL,'CC',NULL,'Data Remediation - ADD MRN Rejected in KPFS and PATDEM',NULL,'1','HD0000002102827',NULL,'2006-12-27 00:00:00',NULL,'2 PM',NULL,'DAT','C',NULL,'L',40,13,'A patient was created in Epic on 12/24/2006 at 1:50 AM and is homed in PRODCCM.  However, the patient\"s first name was entered with a comma and the middle initial, so the A28 add msg and subsequent A31 update msg failed in KPFS and PATDEM due to an invalid name.','I have altered the 2 failed msgs, so that the first name excludes the comma and middle initial and retriggered the msgs to KPFS.  The patient should now be reflected in KPFS and PATDEM.  However, the patient\"s first name still needs to be updated in Epic to exclude the comma and middle initial, which will generate a valid A31 update msg to KPFS.\r\n\r\nThe Epic user that created the patient was Kimberly Hassan (User ID K213460), working in department SSC-ADM* >BRUCEVLL MOB.  I\"ve re-assigned the Remedy ticket to a Prelude AC to edit the patient\"s name in Epic.','','','','','','',40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-03 10:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(13,1,NULL,37,NULL,'CA',0,'A01 Missing for KPADT',NULL,'','HD0000002115440',NULL,'2007-01-01 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,'MSG','C',NULL,'L',43,16,'A01 is missing for a MRN.  The previous admit was cancelled by an A11 and then a user was trying to admit the patient again (admit time # 2007/01/01 22.00) but it failed to trigger a msg.  Also, a discharge message (A03) for this same encounter was triggered, which has also failed (discharge time # 2007/01/02 02.10). Ajish Antony will take a look at this issue from a Bridges perspective.','','','','','','','',40,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-03 10:53:00','2008-05-01 10:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,1,NULL,32,NULL,'CA',NULL,'A KPHC Msg in VMM is Not Closing',NULL,'2','HD0000002113216',NULL,'2007-01-02 00:00:00',NULL,'5:40 PM',NULL,'UNK','C',NULL,'L',40,13,'By looking at the inbound msg from AACC to KPHC and how the Epic DB was updated, I see the following occurred:\r\n\r\nWhen the new msg was received in KPHC from AACC on 12/12 at 3:38PM, an Inbasket msg was triggered to Provider Jennifer Anne Tenney (M.D.).  At 6:01 PM, Jennifer read (Pended) the msg from her Inbasket and then forwarded it to Norma Castano (M.A.), asking Norma to schedule an appt.  The action of forwarding the msg marks it as Done and removes it from Jennifer\"s Inbasket, but it does not trigger an interface msg back to AACC.  A new Inbasket msg is triggered to whoever it was forwarded to (in this case MA Norma Castano) and that person must Done the msg from their Inbasket (by hitting the Done button) to trigger an interface msg back to AACC.  Norma read the forwarded Inbasket msg on 12/14 at 8:58 AM, putting it in a Pend status, which is still the current status of the Inbasket msg today.  Norma needs to Done the msg from her Inbasket to actually trigger an interface msg back to AACC.','This is a workflow issue and it needs to be communicated to the users that forwarding an AACC Inbasket msg to another Epic user will not trigger an interface msg back to AACC to update VMM.  I\"m re-assiging this ticket back to the group I received it from (Remedy group AD CDA AACC IMPLMT), so they can coordinate having the appropriate workflow communicated to the users.  If that\"s not the correct group for this task, the KPHC Ambulatory support group (Remedy group KPHC CN AMBULATORY TECH) should be able to handle.','','','','','','',40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-03 10:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(15,1,NULL,5,NULL,'EB',NULL,'Chart Synch Issue in Prod - High Remedy Ticket',NULL,'','HD0000002130137',NULL,'2007-01-07 00:00:00',NULL,'7:15 PM',NULL,'DAT','C',NULL,'H',40,13,'Remedy Ticket HD0000002130137 was opened on 1/7/07 because multiple facilities were receiving timeout errors when registering or discharging patients.  The issue was found to be related to Chart Synching and the Interconnect queue being backed up.  A PARRS appt msg was received on PRODEBM on 1/5/07 for a patient homed on PRODSBM, so a Chart Synch was required.  However, a portion of the patient\"s Chart Synch record contained special symbols above the ASCII standard character set (extended ASCII display characters), preventing the Chart Synch from completing.  The PARRS msg went into a continual \"wait state\" and the Interconnect (Chart Synch) queue begin to back-up.  So, I killed the appt msg from the incoming PARRS AIHLIN queue and the Chart Synch process for the patient was stopped, allowing all queued msgs on the Interconnect queue to drain.  At this point (8PM), the initial Remedy Ticket was resolved and a new Ticket HD0000002130310 was opened for remediation purposes to clean-up the affected patient\"s rec','','','','','','','',40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-10 10:12:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(16,1,NULL,33,NULL,'AA',0,'Inactivity pages on 2nd Friday of every month due to mainframe',NULL,'.5',NULL,NULL,'2007-01-12 00:00:00',NULL,'4:23 am',NULL,'INT','C',NULL,'L',30,3,'Inactivity pages on incoming lab interface started at 4:23 am.','Scheduled maintenance is being performed on the mainframe to support the monthly release schedule (second Friday of every month from 4 am to 6:30 am).  This affects all mainframe applications such as RILIS, PARRS, and MRMS.','','','','','','',30,38,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-01-16 04:35:00','2008-05-01 10:55:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(19,1,NULL,5,NULL,'NB',NULL,'NBM Storage Upgrade','','','',NULL,'2005-09-12 00:00:00',NULL,'','1900-01-01 00:00:00','INT','C','N','L',37,10,'blah.','Epic code drop.','','','','','','',37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-09-12 00:00:00','2006-11-14 02:41:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(20,1,NULL,5,NULL,'CA',NULL,'Resubmit Failed Appo