hey were getting rejected and caused an undue load on the error queue on the PIMS end. Epic fix (RA124v3) will prevent these DC messages from being sent to PIMS.  \r\n\r\n\r\nRFC 335092 - When PIMS sent a DC message without a DC reason, Bridges was defaulting to \"Adverse Reaction\", which was very misleading. Epic fix (RA201v2) will change the default DC reason to be \"Discontinue Prescription\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-03 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(48,1,NULL,23,NULL,'SB',NULL,'Incoming Lab Filer Crashed',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,40,13,'The incoming Lab filer (AIP 898301) crashed again today in PRODSBM at 10:30 AM.  I had to remove message # 93203 from the queue.  After doing so, I was able to successfully start the filer again.  The ORD record (# 7579182 in SB) that the message is trying to update, is missing item 220 (Patient Visit Dat).  However, in this case, the order was created by the interface on the same instance and it is still missing item 220.  The message that crashed the filer was a result message and not a cancel (which is what we\'ve seen in the past).  The skipped result message did file to the correct ORD record, marking it as final, but then immediately crashed the filer.  It appears that we have a new issue or variation of the old issue.','Aaron Milberger from Epic commented that the message to the Provider\'s inbox is failing and crashing the interface.  More analysis still needs to be done on the Epic side to determine a solution.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(49,1,NULL,12,NULL,'EB',879270,'Reg+ Rejects EEG Registrations',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-09 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,37,10,'Note.. This problem recurrs on almost ever y go-live.  The root cause is that the PRC entries are not set up with the right CPT code in item 4515. \r\n\r\nReg+ edits the CPT code sent in ZEX-28.  Reg+ has a list of what CPT codes are allowed for a dept. \r\n\r\nReg+ does not edit CPT codes if the dept. is ancillary, which will be indicated by PRC-4517 with value 1.   PRC-4517 not present means it is not an ancillary.','Contact Reg+ team… Need to have the EEG cpt codes added for the dept.. .HAY-NEU.. Not clear if this is programming change or administration function.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-09 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(50,1,NULL,4,NULL,'All',NULL,'EMPI Timeout Errors - All Servers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-10 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,29,2,'EMPI Server is down… Bridges getting EMPI 1501 errors on all severs on multiple interfaces.','EMPI server did not complete batch cycle.  Help desk started bridge.  \r\n \r\nAll 1501 errors for KPFS / 898705 and PCLS 898701 were resubmitted on all instances.\r\n\r\nStill need to research lab.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,29,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-10 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(51,1,NULL,19,NULL,'EB',NULL,'False - HC is Setting Patient Status to Discharged',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-08 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,37,10,'Facility reported that HC was setting patient status to discharged when they ordered ER Lab via RILIS.','False report. This was occurring only within RILIS.  IP orders are not live, and there are no orders flowing out of HC.  This was soley a RILIS issue.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-08 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(52,1,NULL,7,NULL,'CA',NULL,'KPFS Outbound - Fix First Name to Remove Comma',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2005-08-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,NULL,15,'User entered comma in first name, and the add rejected in KPFS and PATDEM.\r\n\r\nCorrecting message in the interface, and re-submitting.','Patient appeared in PATDEM.