s Filer Crash',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-03-27 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,29,2,'On 3/26  message 3694886 on interface 898501 crashed the appointments filer at 19:08 on ktazp1956, PRODNBM. \r\nNo cache error was logged from the filer crash. I tried recompiling and restarting the interface but that did change \r\nanything.  I then skipped the message and restarted the interface.  It ran for a while  and then crashed again \r\non message 3694964.  I  tried restarting the interface and again it crashed without producing a cache error. \r\nI then skipped the second message and restarted the interface.   It has remained up since then.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,29,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-03-27 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(171,1,NULL,22,NULL,'All',1393128,'Invalid Substitute Defect - HD1393128',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-13 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,39,12,'A production ticket (HD 1393128)  was opened by Pharmacy team and assigned to our group regarding Epic sending invalid Substitution Allowed value (RXO-9) - On research we had found that provider had entered back slash (\\) at the end of SIG (RXO-7) and it had caused this problem in RXO-9.','\"\r\nThe valid \"Substitution Allowed\" values are N and G which Epic should send in RXO-9. In the message below Epic indeed sent the G in RXO-9 but the problem was in RXO-7 field. That filed ends with \\ which is an escape character. When \\ appear before the pipe character (|) that pipe character is not counted as field separator so the HL7 parser at PIMS would consider it as part of RXO-7 field - eventually G which is in RXO-9 would be considered as in RXO-8 (all fields will be left shifted by one count after that) - Thus RXO-9 will be considered blank by PIMS HL7 parser and it would scream \"Invalid Substitution Allowed Value\".\r\n\"\r\n\r\nSusan had done further research on using special characters like \\, ^ and & and here is her finding:\r\n\r\n\r\n\"\r\n&  in middle of free text -  Okay, unable to edit free text sigs.\r\n^ in middle of text -  Issue cuts of remaining of SIG.  Type in Take 1 tablet ^ orally daily as instructed by MD....PIMS only gets Take 1 tablet orally.\r\n\"\r\n\r\nFix at Epic End\r\n---------------------\r\n\r\nWe have ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-13 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(172,1,NULL,33,NULL,'All',1434058,'MyChart 13 month interface missing provider name',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,39,12,'This problem has been noticed recently in production and many tickets are opened around it. In certain cases the 898711 interface is creating EPT-20 and EPT-30 with correct values but leaves  EPT-7040 blank. Consequently provider\'s names is appearing blank in MyChart. I have looked at the HL7 messages and CDR is sending us provider resources IDs.','This problem has been noticed recently in production and many tickets are opened around it. In certain cases the 898711 interface is creating EPT-20 and EPT-30 with correct values but leaves  EPT-7040 blank. Consequently provider\'s names is appearing blank in MyChart. I have looked at the HL7 messages and CDR is sending us provider resources IDs.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,39,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(173,1,NULL,5,NULL,'EB',1474596,'BP rpts incorrect Visit Type for Prenatal pts',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-19 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,40,13,'PARRS Visit type PNDC. Confirmed as pregnant. No cost associated since included in OB episode. Incorrect type of Visit Navigator initiated (GYN instead of OB).','Sent email to Suzanne Leong:\r\nI was just re-assigned ticket HD0000001474596 from you with the summary \"BP rpts incorr Visit Type for Prenatal pts.\"  However, there is no MRN\'s listed in the ticket at which I can look at.  Please provide some so I can search PA