eceiving and processing messages again across the two impacted interfaces around 11:30AM.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(176,1,NULL,37,NULL,'CA',1482691,'A02 failed because of a bed occupied problem',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,33,6,'A02 failed because of a bed occupied problem. Two MRNs in the same Unit - 5W Room - 5037 Bed - 5037-A.\r\nThe facility is SAC and see confidential info for MRNs.','HC-ADT confirmed that A02 was triggered for the first MRN in confidential info at 9.02 AM. Please investigate, why this A02 did not reach KP-ADT.\r\n\r\nPer Ankur: No A02 was triggered out of Epic for the transfer. Epic is investigating.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,33,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(177,1,NULL,19,NULL,'EB',1489373,'RILIS is not receiving information from Epic',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-24 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,40,13,'RILIS is not receiving information from KPHC.  See confidential for patient information.  Patient Impact:  Patient treatment is being delayed, unable to analyze specimen..  Information released from KPHC is not showing in RILIS.  Did not receive print out lable.  Last release:  5 mins.','Only four patients were impacted. Also, it appears that this is a workstation mapping issue.\r\nUpdate - it has been confirmed that the BP can use adjacent workstation to release orders in KPHC and they will show in RILIS as well as the labels printing. The impacted patients have been reconciled.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-24 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(178,1,NULL,4,NULL,'CC',1490934,'Pt showing in CIPS and KPFS, but not KPHC',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-04-24 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,40,13,'I received a helpdesk ticket about a pt not showing in Epic.  I noticed