aracter and erred in the IB on the staging server.  This text is entered into Epic via a paste anc copy from an Excel spreadsheet.  The IB on the staging server contains a different HL7 parser as opposed to the Prod IB, where the 8 bit charaters are removed and the msgs are then passed on to Pyxis.  The IB group re-pointed the Pyxis msg flow from the staging IB to the Prod IB.  We are researching with Epic on whether they can suppress these 8 bit characters.  This will be a pro',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,40,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-07-16 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(211,1,NULL,36,NULL,'GG',1679106,'Pyxis order 30270139 not making it to Pyxis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2006-07-16 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'INT','C','N',NULL,40,13,'A Pyxis order message triggered from NCAL KPHC on 7/15/06 at 6:31 PM is not making it to Pyxis in SFO.  SFO IP go-live Command Center called Bridges primary support at 1:14PM on 7/16/06 asking if this was the same issue as a previous Pyxis issue (Ticket 1679603).','The issue is with a Pyxis order triggered from NCAL KPHC not making it to Pyxis.  Pyxis order 30270139 left KPHC from the NCAL PRODGGM (AMRO3) instance yesterday, 7/15/06, at 6:31 PM for a patient in SFO.  The Pyxis order msg left Epic and was accepted/acknowledged by the IB (Integration Broker).  The ticket was reassigned to the EIS group who manages the NCAL IB, who found that the smart set text included an 8 bit character and erred in the IB on the staging server.  This text is entered into Epic via a paste anc copy from an Excel spreadsheet.  The IB on the staging server contains a different HL7 parser as opposed to the Prod IB, where the 8 bit charaters are removed and the msgs are then passed on to Pyxis.  The IB group re-pointed the Pyxis msg flow from the staging IB to the Prod IB.  We are researching with Epic on whether they can suppress these 8 bit characters.  This will be a problem with every IP go-live, unless the IB on the staging server 