iets for patient.  See Confidential Info for patient name and MRN.  Please assist.\r\n\r\nInterface shows ADT-A02 transfer to Hayward.... \r\nNo answer on phone # in ticket.','','User was entereing the wrong MRN # in CIPS.','','','','','',37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-06 10:59:00','2007-10-10 09:33:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(245,1,NULL,61,NULL,'NB',2835158,'PCLS Batch Transfer for Deer Valley Cleared About 3,000 PCP',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2007-10-05 00:00:00',NULL,'2:00 AM',NULL,'UNK','C',NULL,'M',37,NULL,'PCLS sent a batch of PCP updates to HC which have cleared out several thousand PCPs.\r\n','','The EMPI failover server was restarted, and it began servicing EMPI requests outside the production proxy service.  This allowed empi looksup to be returned to the IB out-of-order, so the PCP messages came to Bridges out-of-order.','','','','about 3,000 members had their PCP information removed.  This would possibly impact their ability to send on-line message to their PCP if they had not visited the PCP within the last 13 months.','',37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-10 09:44:00','2007-11-02 09:53:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(246,1,NULL,39,NULL,'NB',0,'SYSLOG Errors in NB for BioMed',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2007-10-10 00:00:00',NULL,'2-3 PM',NULL,'UNK','C',NULL,'M',37,NULL,'Unknown syslog errros for the unknown cause - possibly BioMed.\r\n\r\n','','','','','','','',37,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-10-10 09:46:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(247,1,NULL,37,NULL,'NB',0,'A11 Triggered in PRODNBM over ADT with no associated Admit',NULL,'1',NULL,NULL,'2007-11-02 00:00:00',NULL,'2:22pm',NULL,'UNK','C',NULL,'L',43,NULL,'We got an A11 message in EHS that failed en route to Central Process because the Assigned Unit (PV1-3.1) was 6 characters long (4 is the max).  The value was VALRAD.  In addition, there is no sign of this encounter in Event Management. \r\n\r\nHowever, this encounter did have an outpatient check-in and a cancel check-in that went out over the Cadence registration interface.  The cancel was triggered 1 second before the ADT cancel was sent out.  Can you find out why the ADT message was triggered?  Also, why was VALRAD sent in the message? ','A11 message was erroneous.  No need to remediate data.','The reason this occurred is because Kaiser is employing functionality called \"Contact Redirection.\"  Before the Cadence Outpatient check-in was performed into the Rad department at 2:22pm, another Cadence outpatient check-in was initiated for the same patient in the same department at 2:21pm.  HC did a conversion on the 2:21pm check-in and made it an HOV visit and sent an A04 over the ADT interface.  This is the standard functionality.  When the second Cadence check-in into the same department was done at 2:22pm, HC used Contact Redirection to associate this second check-in to the previous one.  Thus, no conversion was done to change this second encounter into an HOV encounter.  When the second encounter was cancelled at 2:25pm, a cancel message was sent over both the Cadence and ADT interfaces.  Since this second encounter was never converted to HOV, the ADT items were removed and the department was pulled from DEP 40 instead of being pulled from ADT items.  This is why VALRAD was sent in the ADT cancel mess','Paul Giam - pgiam@epicsystems.com\r\nAjish Antony - ajish.antony@kp.org\r\nDaniel Hom - daniel.hom@kp.org','','completed','None in this case since message went to EHS.  Other impacts could include extra error messages in Central Process if message is received by ancillary.','',43,43,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2007-11-13 02:00:00','2007-11-13 02:06:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(248,1,NULL,60,NULL,'AA',0,'On-Call Production Support Week 11/28-12/05',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'2007-12-05 00:00:00',NULL,'',NULL,'UNK','C',NULL,'M',44,NULL,'1. High Sev incident HD0000002981212 - IB lost connections to various interfaces  (Sunday 12/02 2.45 pm - 5.00 pm)\r\n2. RCSI testing  -  Support (Monday 1